    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom of the stems are turning this sickly yellow color but the top ones look okay. what's probably going on and how do i fix the soil?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants, while the top ones are still green, is a classic sign of a nutrient deficiency, often related to nitrogen or potassium, or sometimes an overwatering issue. You can try to fix your soil by amending it with a balanced, slow-release organic fertilizer, or by applying a liquid feed specifically designed for tomatoes. If the soil is compacted, gently loosening the top few inches can also help with drainage, which is crucial for these thirsty plants. Remember, a good soil structure is as important as the nutrients themselves!",
